docs.lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE, Md., Dec. 7 -- Consul General Murguiondo of Uruguay affirms the statement he made through The United Associated Presses last Friday to the effect that the reported revolution in Uruguay was of little account. The Consul General was at that time in receipt of a cablegram from Montevideo, the Uruguayan capital, saying that the revolt was unimportant.

headline.main: ALL QUIET IN URUGUAY.; The Recent Revolt Was Quickly Suppressed by the Government.
